{"title_page": "Chakra (JavaScript engine)", "text_new": "{{About|the JavaScript engine used in Microsoft Edge. For the JavaScript engine used in Internet Explorer 9 through 11, see [[Chakra (JScript engine)]]||Chakra (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox Software\n| name                   = Chakra\n| logo                   = \n| screenshot             = \n| caption                = \n| developer              = [[Microsoft]]\n| operating system       = [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[macOS]], [[Linux]]\n| latest release version = v1.11.17\n| latest release date    = {{Start date and age|2020|03|10}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/microsoft/ChakraCore/tags|title=Tags \u00b7 microsoft/ChakraCore \u00b7 GitHub|website=GitHub ChakraCore repository|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n| size                   = \n| programming language   = [[C++]]\n| genre                  = [[JavaScript]] engine\n| license                = [[MIT License]]\n| website                = \n}}\n'''Chakra''' is a [[JavaScript]] engine developed by [[Microsoft]] for its [[Microsoft Edge]] [[web browser]]. It is a [[Fork (software development)|fork]] of the [[Chakra (JScript engine)|JScript engine]] used in [[Internet Explorer]]. Like the [[EdgeHTML|Edge layout engine]] and unlike previous versions in [[Internet Explorer]], the declared intention is that it will reflect the \"Living Web\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Targeting Edge vs. Legacy Engines in JsRT APIs|url=https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn903710(v=vs.94).aspx|accessdate=10 September 2015}}</ref> On December 5, 2015, it was announced that core components of ''Chakra'' will be open-sourced as '''ChakraCore'''.\n\n==Standards support==\nChakra supports [[ECMAScript]] 5.1 with partial support for [[ECMAScript]] 6.<ref>{{cite web|title=Microsoft Edge Platform Status|url=https://dev.modern.ie/platform/status//?filter=f0100001c&search=es6|publisher=Microsoft.com|accessdate=10 September 2015}}{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Open sourcing==\nFollowing an initial announcement on December 5, 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.windows.com/msedgedev/2015/12/05/open-source-chakra-core/|title=Microsoft Edge's JavaScript engine to go open-source|publisher=[[Microsoft]]|accessdate=December 8, 2015|date=2015-12-05}}</ref><ref name=\"ChakraCoreopensourced4\">[http://www.zdnet.com/article/microsoft-open-sources-its-edge-web-browser-javascript-engine-and-plans-to-port-it-to-linux/ Microsoft open sources Edge web browser's JavaScript engine, plans port to Linux] on [[zdnet.com]] by Steven J. Vaughan-Nichols (on January 13, 2016)</ref> Microsoft open sourced the Chakra engine as ChakraCore, including all the key components of the JavaScript engine powering Microsoft Edge on their GitHub page under the [[MIT License]] on January 13, 2016.<ref name=\"ChakraCoreopensourced\">[http://www.zdnet.com/article/microsoft-open-sources-its-edge-web-browser-javascript-engine-and-plans-to-port-it-to-linux/ Microsoft open sources Edge web browser's JavaScript engine, plans port to Linux] on [[zdnet.com]] by Steven J. Vaughan-Nichols (on January 13, 2016)</ref><ref>[https://github.com/Microsoft/ChakraCore ChakraCore] on [[github.com]]</ref> ChakraCore is essentially the same as the Chakra engine that powers the [[Microsoft Edge]] browser, but with platform-agnostic bindings, i.e. without the specific interfaces utilised within the [[Universal Windows Platform apps|Universal Windows App]] platform.\n\nMicrosoft has also created a project on [[GitHub]] that allows [[Node.js]] to use ChakraCore as its JavaScript engine instead of [[V8 (JavaScript engine)|V8]].<ref>[https://github.com/Microsoft/node Node.js enabled for ChakraCore] on github.com</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Free and open-source software}}\n* [[Microsoft Edge]]\n* [[JavaScript engine]]\n* [[JScript]]\n* [[Chakra (JScript engine)]]\n* [[ECMAScript]]\n* [[List of ECMAScript engines]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{github|https://github.com/microsoft/ChakraCore}}\n\n{{ECMAScript}}\n{{Microsoft}}\n{{Microsoft FOSS}}\n\n[[Category:JavaScript engines]]\n[[Category:Microsoft free software]]\n\n{{Internet-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{About|the JavaScript engine used in Microsoft Edge. For the JavaScript engine used in Internet Explorer 9 through 11, see [[Chakra (JScript engine)]]||Chakra (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox Software\n| name                   = Chakra\n| logo                   = \n| screenshot             = \n| caption                = \n| developer              = [[Microsoft]]\n| operating system       = [[Linux]], [[macOS]], [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]]\n| latest release version = v1.11.15\n| latest release date    = {{Start date and age|2019|11|12}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/microsoft/ChakraCore/tags|title=Tags \u00b7 microsoft/ChakraCore \u00b7 GitHub|website=GitHub ChakraCore repository|language=en|access-date=2020-01-27}}</ref>\n| size                   = \n| programming language   = \n| genre                  = [[JavaScript]] engine\n| license                = [[MIT License]]\n| website                = \n}}\n'''Chakra''' is a [[JavaScript]] engine developed by [[Microsoft]] for its [[Microsoft Edge]] [[web browser]]. It is a [[Fork (software development)|fork]] of the [[Chakra (JScript engine)|JScript engine]] used in [[Internet Explorer]]. Like the [[EdgeHTML|Edge layout engine]] and unlike previous versions in [[Internet Explorer]], the declared intention is that it will reflect the \"Living Web\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Targeting Edge vs. Legacy Engines in JsRT APIs|url=https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn903710(v=vs.94).aspx|accessdate=10 September 2015}}</ref> On December 5, 2015, it was announced that core components of ''Chakra'' will be open-sourced as '''ChakraCore'''.\n\n==Standards support==\nChakra supports [[ECMAScript]] 5.1 with partial support for [[ECMAScript]] 6.<ref>{{cite web|title=Microsoft Edge Platform Status|url=https://dev.modern.ie/platform/status//?filter=f0100001c&search=es6|publisher=Microsoft.com|accessdate=10 September 2015}}{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Open sourcing==\nFollowing an initial announcement on December 5, 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.windows.com/msedgedev/2015/12/05/open-source-chakra-core/|title=Microsoft Edge's JavaScript engine to go open-source|publisher=[[Microsoft]]|accessdate=December 8, 2015|date=2015-12-05}}</ref><ref name=\"ChakraCoreopensourced4\">[http://www.zdnet.com/article/microsoft-open-sources-its-edge-web-browser-javascript-engine-and-plans-to-port-it-to-linux/ Microsoft open sources Edge web browser's JavaScript engine, plans port to Linux] on [[zdnet.com]] by Steven J. Vaughan-Nichols (on January 13, 2016)</ref> Microsoft open sourced the Chakra engine as ChakraCore, including all the key components of the JavaScript engine powering Microsoft Edge on their GitHub page under the [[MIT License]] on January 13, 2016.<ref name=\"ChakraCoreopensourced\">[http://www.zdnet.com/article/microsoft-open-sources-its-edge-web-browser-javascript-engine-and-plans-to-port-it-to-linux/ Microsoft open sources Edge web browser's JavaScript engine, plans port to Linux] on [[zdnet.com]] by Steven J. Vaughan-Nichols (on January 13, 2016)</ref><ref>[https://github.com/Microsoft/ChakraCore ChakraCore] on [[github.com]]</ref> ChakraCore is essentially the same as the Chakra engine that powers the [[Microsoft Edge]] browser, but with platform-agnostic bindings, i.e. without the specific interfaces utilised within the [[Universal Windows Platform apps|Universal Windows App]] platform.\n\nMicrosoft has also created a project on [[GitHub]] that allows [[Node.js]] to use ChakraCore as its JavaScript engine instead of [[V8 (JavaScript engine)|V8]].<ref>[https://github.com/Microsoft/node Node.js enabled for ChakraCore] on github.com</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Free and open-source software}}\n* [[Microsoft Edge]]\n* [[JavaScript engine]]\n* [[JScript]]\n* [[Chakra (JScript engine)]]\n* [[ECMAScript]]\n* [[List of ECMAScript engines]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{github|https://github.com/microsoft/ChakraCore}}\n\n{{ECMAScript}}\n{{Microsoft}}\n{{Microsoft FOSS}}\n\n[[Category:JavaScript engines]]\n[[Category:Microsoft free software]]\n\n{{Internet-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ghettoblaster", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chakra_(JavaScript_engine)"}
{"title_page": "Pietro Chesi", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian cyclist}}\n\n{{Infobox cyclist\n|name = Pietro Chesi\n|image = \n|image_size = \n|caption = \n|fullname = Pietro Chesi\n|nickname = Pelo\n|birth_date = {{Birth date|1902|11|24|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Gambassi Terme]]\n|death_date = {{Death date and age|1944|8|15|1902|11|24|df=y}}\n|death_place = [[Florence]]\n|height = \n|weight = \n|currentteam = \n|discipline = Road\n|role = Rider\n|ridertype = \n|amateuryears1 = \n|amateurteam1 = \n|amateuryears2 = \n|proyears1 = 1927\n|amateurteam2 = \n|proteam1 = Nicolo Biondo\n|proyears2 = 1928\n|proteam2 = [[Bianchi (cycling team)|Bianchi-Pirelli]]\n|proyears3 = 1930\n|proteam3 = Morozzi\n|manageyears1 = \n|manageteam1 = \n|majorwins = [[Milan\u2013San Remo]] (1927)\n|medaltemplates = \n|show-medals = \n}}\n'''Pietro Chesi''' ({{IPA-it|\u02c8pie\u02d0tro \u02c8ke\u02d0zi}}; 24 November 1902 in [[Gambassi Terme]] - 15 August 1944 in [[Florence]]) was an Italian cyclist.\n\nHe was a professional from 1925 to 1934 and won [[Milan\u2013San Remo]] in 1927 with an attack on the [[Passo del Turchino]]. He left the favorite to win, Alfred Binda 9 minutes behind.\n\nHe died when he was shot by anti-fascist partisans.<ref name=\"Memoire du Cyclisme\">{{Cite web | url=http://memoire-du-cyclisme.eu/pelotons/coureurs.php?c=21562 | title=CHESI Pietro \"Pelo\" | accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Palmar\u00e8s==\n;1927\n:[[Milan\u2013San Remo]]\n\n;1928\n:6th overall [[Milan\u2013San Remo]]\n:10th overall [[Giro d'Italia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Milan\u2013San Remo winners}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chesi, Pietro}}\n[[Category:1902 births]]\n[[Category:1944 deaths]]\n[[Category:Italian male cyclists]]\n\n\n{{Italy-cycling-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Infobox cyclist\n|name = Pietro Chesi\n|image = \n|image_size = \n|caption = \n|fullname = Pietro Chesi\n|nickname = Pelo\n|birth_date = {{Birth date|1902|11|24|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Gambassi Terme]]\n|death_date = {{Death date and age|1944|8|15|1902|11|24|df=y}}\n|death_place = [[Florence]]\n|height = \n|weight = \n|currentteam = \n|discipline = Road\n|role = Rider\n|ridertype = \n|amateuryears1 = \n|amateurteam1 = \n|amateuryears2 = \n|proyears1 = 1927\n|amateurteam2 = \n|proteam1 = Nicolo Biondo\n|proyears2 = 1928\n|proteam2 = [[Bianchi (cycling team)|Bianchi-Pirelli]]\n|proyears3 = 1930\n|proteam3 = Morozzi\n|manageyears1 = \n|manageteam1 = \n|majorwins = [[Milan\u2013San Remo]] (1927)\n|medaltemplates = \n|show-medals = \n}}\n'''Pietro Chesi''' ({{IPA-it|\u02c8pie\u02d0tro \u02c8ke\u02d0zi}}; 24 November 1902 in [[Gambassi Terme]] - 15 August 1944 in [[Florence]]) was an Italian cyclist.\n\nHe was a professional from 1925 to 1934 and won [[Milan\u2013San Remo]] in 1927 with an attack on the [[Passo del Turchino]]. He left the favorite to win, Alfred Binda 9 minutes behind.\n\nHe died when he was shot by anti-fascist partisans.<ref name=\"Memoire du Cyclisme\">{{Cite web | url=http://memoire-du-cyclisme.eu/pelotons/coureurs.php?c=21562 | title=CHESI Pietro \"Pelo\" | accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Palmar\u00e8s==\n;1927\n:[[Milan\u2013San Remo]]\n\n;1928\n:6th overall [[Milan\u2013San Remo]]\n:10th overall [[Giro d'Italia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Milan\u2013San Remo winners}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chesi, Pietro}}\n[[Category:1902 births]]\n[[Category:1944 deaths]]\n[[Category:Italian male cyclists]]\n\n\n{{Italy-cycling-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lepricavark", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:added short description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pietro_Chesi"}
